  "market_context": "After a large 500-point daily decline in NQ (from ~18300 to ~17750), the market entered a low-volatility phase with no significant news, forming an indecision candle on the 15-minute chart.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst observed a small-body candle with long wicks on both sides following a large-range expansion, indicating lack of directional conviction and market indecision.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the prior large range expansion—500-point decline in NQ from near 18300 to 17750 on the daily timeframe.",
    "Step 2: Observe the subsequent 15-minute candle: small body, long upper and lower wicks, open and close very close to each other.",
    "Step 3: Interpret this as an indecision candle signaling no real direction, consistent with post-expansion consolidation behavior.",
    "Step 4: Compare to other examples (gold, CL) to confirm the pattern: after large moves, markets often form broadening formations or indecision candles before resuming trend or reversing."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "After a large-range expansion, an indecision candle signals exhaustion and lack of follow-through; traders should avoid directional entries until a clear change in state of delivery or protected swing forms.",
